# Implementation Plan - Phase 12 Refinements: Navigation & Shortcuts

Enhance the slide preview interface with full keyboard support and refined styling for blank slides.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The shortcut logic will work as follows:
> - **Numbers 1-9**: Jumps directly to V1, V2, etc.
> - **Letters (V, C, B)**: Cycles through all slides of that type (e.g., pressing 'V' repeatedly goes V1 -> V2 -> V3 -> V1).
> - **Arrow Keys**: Moves to the immediate next or previous slide.
> Does this cycle logic for 'V' match your workflow?

## Proposed Changes

### State Management

#### [MODIFY] [live_projector_providers.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/live_controller/presentation/live_projector_providers.dart)
- Introduce `currentSlidesProvider` to manage the list of `Slide` objects.
- Introduce `activeSlideIndexProvider` (integer) to track the current position.
- Update `activeSlideProvider` to be a derived provider that returns the content of the slide at `activeSlideIndex`.

### Keyboard Support

#### [MODIFY] [preview_pane.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/dashboard/presentation/widgets/preview_pane.dart)
- Wrap the `PreviewPane` in a `Focus` and `KeyboardListener` widget.
- Implement `onKeyEvent` logic:
    - `LogicalKeyboardKey.arrowDown` / `arrowUp`: Incremental navigation.
    - `LogicalKeyboardKey.digit1` through `digit9`: Jump to `V1`-`V9`.
    - `LogicalKeyboardKey.keyV`: Cycle through all `V` shortcuts.
    - `LogicalKeyboardKey.keyC`: Cycle through all `C` shortcuts.
    - `LogicalKeyboardKey.keyB`: Cycle through all `B` shortcuts.

### UI Styling

#### [MODIFY] [slide_item_widget.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/dashboard/presentation/widgets/slide_item_widget.dart)
- Update `build` method to check `slide.isBlank`.
- If true, return a single `Container` with centered `Text("[ BLANK SCREEN ]")`, effectively "merging" the 3 columns into one.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Logic tests for the shortcut cycling algorithm.

### Manual Verification
1. Select a song in the library.
2. Verify that clicking the slides pane enables keyboard control.
3. Press **Down Arrow** to navigate through the song.
4. Press **'1'** and **'2'** to jump to specific verses.
5. Press **'C'** multiple times if there are multiple choruses to verify cycling.
6. Check the **Blank Slide** at the bottom to ensure it spans the full width of the item.
